<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="560" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1180,1675]" pageId="1" pageNumber="560">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,582,1180,1206]" pageId="1" pageNumber="560">Diagnosis (Guerin-Meneville, 1844):</emphasis>
Body slender, long; vertex produced, frontal rostrum short; large head, with very prominent eyes and three small, inconspicuous ocelli placed on the protruding part of the forehead. Antennae are very fine, twice as long as the body, with the first segment large. Medium sized palpi, the maxillae of four segments almost equal in length, the 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[545,561,1288,1302]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="560">nd</superScript>
and 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[631,645,1288,1302]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="560">rd</superScript>
a little thicker, the last a little longer, elongated and oval. Pronotum is short, wider than long. Tegmina shorter than the abdomen, with longitudinal outer ribs, dorsally reticulated, reaching a little beyond half the abdomen in both sexes, tegmina twice as long as wide, rounded at the apices; males with long hind wings. Ovipositor almost as long as the body, raised and having its tip curved below. Hind legs are very large, finely serrated on their outer sides and having long spines from the middle to the end. Tarsi of three segments, terminated by two large serrated hooks in combs. Claw inner margin has 4 to 5 teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1180,1675]" pageId="1" pageNumber="560">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,361,1504,1530]" pageId="1" pageNumber="560">Composition:</emphasis>
The generic name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guerin-Meneville" authorityYear="1844" box="[578,688,1505,1530]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Euscyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[578,688,1505,1530]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="560">Euscyrtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was established by Guerin-Meneville, 1844 for the first time with 
<taxonomicName authority="Guerin-Meneville, 1844" authorityName="Guerin-Meneville" authorityYear="1844" box="[151,648,1540,1566]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Euscyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bivittatus">
<emphasis box="[151,372,1540,1566]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="560">Euscyrtus bivittatus</emphasis>
Guerin-Meneville, 1844
</taxonomicName>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[724,772,1541,1567]" pageId="1" pageNumber="560">type</typeStatus>
species by original designation. At present genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guerin-Meneville" authorityYear="1844" box="[1326,1436,1541,1566]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Euscyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1326,1436,1541,1566]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="560">Euscyrtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is divided into two subgenera, namely 
<taxonomicName authority="Guerin-Meneville, 1844" authorityName="Guerin-Meneville" authorityYear="1844" box="[590,979,1576,1602]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Euscyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[590,700,1577,1602]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="560">Euscyrtus</emphasis>
Guerin-Meneville, 1844
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorochov, 1987" authorityName="Gorochov" authorityYear="1987" box="[1036,1283,1576,1602]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Euscyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="565" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Osus">
<emphasis box="[1036,1092,1576,1602]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="560">Osus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gorochov, A. V." box="[1099,1283,1576,1602]" pageId="1" pageNumber="560" pagination="1 - 192" refId="ref7041" refString="Gorochov, A. V. (1987) On the fauna of Orthoptera subfamilies Euscyrtinae, Trigonidiidae and Oecanthinae (Orthoptera, Gryllidae) from eastern Indochina. Entomofauna V'etnama [Entomofauna of Vietnam], 1987, 1 - 192." type="journal article" year="1987">Gorochov, 1987</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Gorochov, A. V." box="[151,344,1612,1638]" pageId="1" pageNumber="560" pagination="1 - 192" refId="ref7041" refString="Gorochov, A. V. (1987) On the fauna of Orthoptera subfamilies Euscyrtinae, Trigonidiidae and Oecanthinae (Orthoptera, Gryllidae) from eastern Indochina. Entomofauna V'etnama [Entomofauna of Vietnam], 1987, 1 - 192." type="journal article" year="1987">Gorochov (1987)</bibRefCitation>
external morphological differences are not significant; however, the main difference is in the male genitalic structure. The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guerin-Meneville" authorityYear="1844" box="[489,599,1649,1674]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Euscyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[489,599,1649,1674]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="560">Euscyrtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has about 21 known species all over the world (
<bibRefCitation author="Cigliano, M. M. &amp; Braun, H. &amp; Eades, D. &amp; Otte, D." box="[1139,1375,1648,1675]" pageId="1" pageNumber="560" refId="ref6956" refString="Cigliano, M. M., Braun, H., Eades, D. C &amp; Otte, D. (2020) Orthoptera Species file. version 5.0 / 5.0. Available from: http: // Orthoptera. Speciesfile. org (accessed 20 July 2020)" type="url" year="2020">
Cigliano 
<emphasis box="[1244,1293,1648,1674]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="560">et al</emphasis>
., 2020
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
